04/06/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- Athens Mayor Dora Bakoyianni said on Thursday (3 June) that her city would be ready for the Summer Olympics by 1 August. She was on a trip to New York and Washington to promote the city and the Games. New York, one of the stops for the Olympic Flame, is bidding to host the 2012 Olympics.
In other news, a Greek daily reported Thursday that authorities have agreed to allow armed guards from the United States, Britain and Israel to accompany their countries' teams. But Greek police denied the report, saying that the government's official position banning armed guards still stands. (AP, AFP, Bloomberg, ANA, Greece - 03/06/04)
